=head1 DESCRIPTION

Represents a harvest job resource in MediaPackage v2, which is used to
export content from an origin endpoint to an S3 bucket.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Arn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ChannelGroupName => Str

The name of the channel group containing the channel associated with
this harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ChannelName => Str

The name of the channel associated with this harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CreatedAt => Str

The date and time when the harvest job was created.


=head2 Description => Str

An optional description of the harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Destination => L<Paws::MediaPackageV2::Destination>

The S3 destination where the harvested content will be placed.


=head2 ErrorMessage => Str

An error message if the harvest job encountered any issues.


=head2 ETag => Str

The current version of the harvest job. Used for concurrency control.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> HarvestedManifests => L<Paws::MediaPackageV2::HarvestedManifests>

A list of manifests that are being or have been harvested.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> HarvestJobName => Str

The name of the harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ModifiedAt => Str

The date and time when the harvest job was last modified.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> OriginEndpointName => Str

The name of the origin endpoint associated with this harvest job.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> ScheduleConfiguration => L<Paws::MediaPackageV2::HarvesterScheduleConfiguration>

The configuration for when the harvest job is scheduled to run.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

The current status of the harvest job (e.g., QUEUED, IN_PROGRESS,
CANCELLED, COMPLETED, FAILED).



